line_1: The horrid notes my refluent waters daunt,
line_2: The Echoes groan, the Dryads quit their haunt;

line_1: Not thy disdain my love could daunt;
line_2: Thro' years of wrong, and years of want;

line_1: When famine leads, what thing can daunt,
line_2: Each mouse was as the mastiff gaunt,
